The paper deals with optimization techniques for neural networks and analyzes the loss landscape of these networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the impact of batch normalization on the loss landscape, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper uses datasets such as FashionMNIST and CIFAR10, which could also place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category.
